This patch renames a single metrics counter in the Javelin Steno Pico split firmware from `RESET_COUNT` to `SPLIT_RESET_COUNT` in the connection failure handler. The change occurs in `PicoSplit::SplitData::OnReceiveFailed()`, which resets state when the wireless link between keyboard halves drops. The counter increment happens after clearing connection state but before reinitializing buffers. This is a straightforward enum constant rename; any code that reads or aggregates this specific metric must use the new name or lose tracking of split resets.